The paper deals with algorithmic techniques for estimating graph parameters in the context of random order streams, which suggests that it belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) categories. The specific problems addressed in the paper, such as estimating the number of connected components, the weight of a minimum spanning tree, and the size of a maximum independent set, are all related to fundamental graph algorithms, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms (cs.AL). Finally, the paper involves the use of information theory techniques, such as the Fano inequality, which suggests that it could also be classified under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
